Start a file with what?

/etc/mime.types     global configs for data types
/etc/mailcap        global config for programs
.mime.types         local config for data types
.mailcap            local config for programs

types       type    file name      
mailcap     type; open with (semicolon is separator)

## Files without *.type
The program 'file' tries to read the file type. Some
distros in /etc/magic ~ .magic changeable. 